<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/54572907-jeffrey-w-brigham"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1459741023i/54572907._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/54572907-jeffrey-w-brigham">Jeffrey W Brigham</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">It&apos;s violent, bloody. I don&apos;t believe the author wrote this with the intention of having the 8th graders of the world studying it. The dialogue is bru<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">It's violent, bloody. I don't believe the author wrote this with the intention of having the 8th graders of the world studying it. The dialogue is brutally hard to understand and must really be read closely. Plenty of other stuff for 8th graders to read, so I'd find something else. High school would be more appropriate I think.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
