<span id="freeTextContainer11041574336528196316">Stephen Crane was an American novelist, poet and journalist, best known for the novel <i>The Red Badge of Courage</i>. That work introduced the reading world to Crane&apos;s striking prose, a mix of impressionism, naturalism and symbolism. He died at age 28 in Badenweiler, Baden, Germany.<br/><br/></span>
  <span id="freeText11041574336528196316" style="display:none">Stephen Crane was an American novelist, poet and journalist, best known for the novel <i>The Red Badge of Courage</i>. That work introduced the reading world to Crane's striking prose, a mix of impressionism, naturalism and symbolism. He died at age 28 in Badenweiler, Baden, Germany.<br /><br /></span>
